description.narrative: The national system is strengthened for vulnerable children to access integrated and inclusive social protection services., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluation, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment and systems for disadvantaged and excluded children, guided by data and knowledge.

title.narrative: The national system is strengthened for vulnerable children to access integrated and inclusive social protection services.

description.narrative: Technical assistance to the NAF contributed to including over 640,000 children in the national safety net during 2021. NAF beneficiaries are being linked to the Makani integrated package of social service through the Takaful ‘Plus’ initiative jointly launched by UNICEF and NAF.The UNICEF humanitarian cash assistance programme, Hajati, continued its monthly cash transfers reaching 22,000 children, whilst also achieving stronger linkages with Makani. ;Makani revamped its programme introducing blended learning, and a market-driven skill building programme. Over 130,000 children, and parents from vulnerable regions and communities (including ITS, DOM, and Ex-Gazans) were covered by Makani services in 2021. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2022
